In the referendum in Macedonia, violations were recorded
Four incidents related to violations of electoral law were registered in the Republic of Macedonia in a referendum on an intergovernmental treaty with Greece on renaming.
This was reported on Sunday by the press secretary of the Ministry of Internal Affairs Tony Angelovsky.
Since the opening of polling stations, 4 incidents have been recorded, which have been eliminated, he said.
At the polling station in the elementary school "Lazo Angelovski" in Skopje, 22-year-old K.J. violated public order and tranquility, insulted citizens and attacked police.
